<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-740-300  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 740 300.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Personal Computing  Oct 1989 v13 n10 p216(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>What corporate America wants from PCs. (Commentary)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ashton, Alan C.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Corporate America wants computer software systems that match itsneeds, but not all these needs are the same.andP;  Corporations mustpurchase systems that will grow with their organizations.andP;  At thesame time, companies must choose software that works on existingcomputers, as well as on newer, faster computers.andP;  Corporationsneed fully featured software that will increase productivity, andprograms for which many people have already been trained.andP;  Anothercommon corporate need is to have document and data conversioncapabilities that are compatible with a number of platforms aswell as with different computer applications.andP;  However, acorporation's primary requirement is to find and installintegrated solutions that work well together.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     CompaniesUser NeedsMicrocomputersDecision MakingCompatibilityData ConversionIntegrated ApproachSoftware packagesSoftware Selection.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>